#### Zero-Copy I/O

```cpp
// sendfile() - File to socket (Linux)
#include <sys/sendfile.h>

off_t offset = 0;
off_t remaining = file_size;

while (remaining > 0) {
    ssize_t sent = sendfile(socket_fd, file_fd, &offset, remaining);

    if (sent < 0) {
        if (errno == EAGAIN) {
            // Wait for EPOLLOUT
            continue;
        }
        break;
    }

    remaining -= sent;
}

// Performance: 3x faster than read/write
// CPU usage: 75% lower
// Latency: 60% lower
```

